In [[British politics]], the '''Shadow Home Secretary''' is the person within the [[Official Opposition Shadow Cabinet (UK)|shadow cabinet]] who 'shadows' the [[Home Secretary]]; this effectively means scrutinising government policy on home affairs including [[policing]], [[national security]], [[immigration]], the [[criminal justice system]], the [[prison|prison service]], and matters of [[citizenship]]. If and when the opposition party is elected to government, the Shadow Home Secretary often becomes the new [[Home Secretary]] though this is not always the case. The present Shadow Home Secretary is [[Yvette Cooper]].
